Real good, Phil.

729
01:00:27,723 --> 01:00:29,350
He's crazy.

730
01:00:33,963 --> 01:00:37,262
I'm worried. I think there's something
really wrong with Phil.

731
01:00:37,333 --> 01:00:39,927
There's a lot of things
really wrong with Phil.

732
01:00:44,140 --> 01:00:46,404
I've come to the end of me.

733
01:00:46,475 --> 01:00:49,842
There's no way out now.

734
01:00:49,912 --> 01:00:53,370
I just want you to remember
we had a beautiful day together once.

735
01:00:56,685 --> 01:01:00,246
All right, little fella.
Good job.

736
01:01:00,322 --> 01:01:02,916
- He smiled at me. Did you see that?
- I believe he did.

737
01:01:04,560 --> 01:01:06,721
Okay, little fella.
There you go.

738
01:01:09,298 --> 01:01:11,698
Hi, mister.
Something I can do you for?

739
01:01:14,370 --> 01:01:16,304
What are you doing?

740
01:01:20,976 --> 01:01:23,137
Jake, get the word out!
Somebody kidnapped Phil!

741
01:01:23,212 --> 01:01:24,770
We're going after him!

742
01:01:31,287 --> 01:01:34,313
Why would anybody steal a groundhog?

743
01:01:34,390 --> 01:01:37,382
I can probably think
of a couple of reasons. Pervert.

744
01:02:03,185 --> 01:02:06,712
- He must have just snapped!
- This should be good.

745
01:02:09,191 --> 01:02:12,126
What is he doing?
What can he be thinking?

746
01:02:12,194 --> 01:02:14,594
That's not bad
for a quadruped.

747
01:02:14,663 --> 01:02:18,497
You gotta check your mirrors,
just the side of your eye.

748
01:02:24,440 --> 01:02:26,203
That's it.

749
01:02:26,275 --> 01:02:28,869
They're chasing us!
Come on, make it fun!

750
01:02:37,386 --> 01:02:40,184
Don't drive angry.

751
01:03:00,176 --> 01:03:04,772
Hot dog! There's no way out except
the way we came in. We got him now!

752
01:03:23,732 --> 01:03:26,530
- What is he doing?
- I don't know.

753
01:03:30,639 --> 01:03:33,665
If you gotta shoot, aim high.
I don't wanna hit the groundhog.

754
01:03:38,013 --> 01:03:40,243
We mustn't keep
our public waiting.

755
01:03:43,419 --> 01:03:44,886
It's show time.

756
01:03:51,160 --> 01:03:53,594
All right, on me, Larry,
in three!

757
01:03:55,030 --> 01:03:58,591
Two, one.

758
01:04:15,451 --> 01:04:16,918
He might be okay.

759
01:04:21,624 --> 01:04:24,115
Probably not now.

760
01:04:39,842 --> 01:04:41,867
Nuts.

761
01:04:48,917 --> 01:04:52,284
Did you sleep well, Mr. Connors?

762
01:04:52,354 --> 01:04:55,949
Would you like some toast?

763
01:05:13,842 --> 01:05:17,403
- What's going on?
- My God.

764
01:05:49,678 --> 01:05:51,111
That's him.

765
01:05:54,116 --> 01:05:57,779
He was a really great guy.

766
01:05:57,853 --> 01:06:00,686
I really liked him a lot.

767
01:06:08,163 --> 01:06:08,297
I'm sorry.
What was that again?

768
01:06:08,297 --> 01:06:10,424
I'm sorry.
What was that again?

769
01:06:10,466 --> 01:06:13,560
- I'm a god!
- You're a god?

770
01:06:13,635 --> 01:06:17,002
I'm a god.
I'm not the God, I don't think.

771
01:06:17,072 --> 01:06:19,666
Because you survived a car wreck?

772
01:06:19,742 --> 01:06:21,334
You ready to order?

773
01:06:21,410 --> 01:06:24,573
I didn't just survive a wreck.
I wasn't just blown up yesterday.

774
01:06:24,646 --> 01:06:27,513
I have been stabbed,
shot, poisoned...

775
01:06:27,583 --> 01:06:30,518
frozen, hung, electrocuted...

776
01:06:30,586 --> 01:06:32,850
- and burned.
- Really?

777
01:06:32,921 --> 01:06:37,688
Every morning I wake up fine,
not a dent in the fender.

778
01:06:37,760 --> 01:06:41,719
- I am an immortal.
- Special today is blueberry waffles.

779
01:06:41,797 --> 01:06:43,788
Why are you telling me this?

780
01:06:43,866 --> 01:06:46,198
Because I want you
to believe in me.

781
01:06:46,268 --> 01:06:51,365
You're not a god. Believe me. This is
12 years of Catholic school talking.

782
01:06:51,440 --> 01:06:53,874
I could come back
if you're not ready.

783
01:06:53,942 --> 01:06:56,240
How do you know I'm not a god?

784
01:06:56,311 --> 01:07:00,145
Please!
Because it's not possible!

785
01:07:00,215 --> 01:07:03,275
- I'll come back.
- Doris!

786
01:07:07,156 --> 01:07:09,920
This is Doris. Her brother-in-law,
Carl, owns this diner.

787
01:07:09,992 --> 01:07:14,554
She's worked here since she was 17.
She wants to see Paris before she dies.

788
01:07:14,630 --> 01:07:17,030
- Boy, would I!
- What are you doing?

789
01:07:17,099 --> 01:07:20,660
- Debbie Kleiser and her fiance, Fred.
- Do I know you?

790
01:07:20,736 --> 01:07:23,864
They're supposed to be married this
afternoon, but Debbie is reconsidering.

791
01:07:23,939 --> 01:07:26,908
- What?
- Lovely ring.

792
01:07:26,975 --> 01:07:29,170
This is Bill who's been a waiter
for three years...

793
01:07:29,244 --> 01:07:31,735
since he left Penn State
and had to get work.

794
01:07:31,814 --> 01:07:34,647
He likes the town, paints toy soldiers,
and he's gay.

795
01:07:34,716 --> 01:07:36,581
I am.

796
01:07:36,652 --> 01:07:39,746
This is Gus. He hates his life here
and wishes he'd stayed in the Navy.

797
01:07:39,822 --> 01:07:42,484
I could have retired on half pay
after 20 years.

798
01:07:42,558 --> 01:07:44,617
Is this some kind of trick?

799
01:07:44,693 --> 01:07:47,594
Maybe the real God uses tricks.
Maybe He's not omnipotent.

800
01:07:47,663 --> 01:07:50,791
He's just been around so long,
He knows everything.

801
01:07:50,866 --> 01:07:52,299
- Who's that?
- This is Tom.

802
01:07:52,367 --> 01:07:54,597
He worked in the coal mine
till they closed it down.

803
01:07:54,670 --> 01:07:56,103
- Her?
- Alice.

804
01:07:56,171 --> 01:07:58,799
She came from Ireland as a baby
and lived in Erie most of her life.

805
01:07:58,874 --> 01:08:01,001
- He's right.
- Nancy.

806
01:08:01,076 --> 01:08:05,809
She works in the dress shop and makes
chipmunk noises when she gets excited.

807
01:08:05,881 --> 01:08:07,815
- It's true.
- How do you know these people?

808
01:08:07,883 --> 01:08:12,684
I know everything. In five seconds,
a waiter will drop a tray of dishes.

809
01:08:12,754 --> 01:08:15,552
- Five, four, three, two, one.
- This is nuts.

810
01:08:18,327 --> 01:08:19,760
That's enough.

811
01:08:21,396 --> 01:08:25,196
- Do you know me too?
- I know all about you.

812
01:08:25,267 --> 01:08:28,065
You like producing, but you're hoping
for more than Channel 9 Pittsburgh.

813
01:08:28,136 --> 01:08:30,661
Everyone knows that.

814
01:08:30,739 --> 01:08:34,004
You like boats, but not the ocean.

815
01:08:34,076 --> 01:08:37,637
You go to a mountain lake in the summer
with your family.

816
01:08:37,713 --> 01:08:39,738
There's a long, wooden dock
and a boathouse...

817
01:08:39,815 --> 01:08:41,840
with boards missing
from the roof...

818
01:08:41,917 --> 01:08:45,250
and a place you used to crawl
underneath to be alone.

819
01:08:45,320 --> 01:08:49,689
You're a sucker for French poetry
and rhinestones.

820
01:08:49,758 --> 01:08:51,487
You're very generous.

821
01:08:51,593 --> 01:08:54,426
You're kind to strangers
and children.

822
01:08:54,530 --> 01:08:57,363
And when you stand in the snow,
you look like an angel.

823
01:08:57,399 --> 01:08:59,367
How are you doing this?

824
01:09:00,469 --> 01:09:05,372
I wake up every day right here...

825
01:09:05,407 --> 01:09:08,934
in Punxsutawney,
and it's always February 2.

826
01:09:10,012 --> 01:09:12,412
There's nothing
I can do about it.

827
01:09:13,282 --> 01:09:16,410
If you still doubt me...

828
01:09:16,485 --> 01:09:18,976
in ten seconds...

829
01:09:19,054 --> 01:09:22,751
Larry will come through that door
and take you away from me...

830
01:09:22,824 --> 01:09:25,520
but you can't let him.

831
01:09:25,627 --> 01:09:28,596
Please believe me.
You've got to believe me.

832
01:09:33,769 --> 01:09:37,705
You ready? We better get going if we're
going to stay ahead of the weather.

833
01:09:37,773 --> 01:09:40,037
What's that?

834
01:09:48,517 --> 01:09:50,451
Maybe it really is happening.

835
01:09:50,519 --> 01:09:52,646
How else could you know so much?

836
01:09:52,721 --> 01:09:55,212
There is no way.
I'm not that smart.

837
01:09:56,391 --> 01:09:58,825
Maybe I should spend the day
with you...

838
01:09:58,894 --> 01:10:02,421
as an objective witness,
just to see what happens.

839
01:10:02,464 --> 01:10:05,228
This sounds
like a science project.

840
01:10:06,201 --> 01:10:08,897
Concentrate.
You gotta want it.

841
01:10:12,541 --> 01:10:16,272
It's more in the wrist than the finger.
It's just gotta...

842
01:10:24,553 --> 01:10:26,487
Be the hat! Come on! Go!

843
01:10:26,555 --> 01:10:28,489
It would take me a year
to get good at this.

844
01:10:28,557 --> 01:10:33,119
Six months. Four to five hours a day,
and you'd be an expert.

845
01:10:33,195 --> 01:10:35,527
Is this what you do
with eternity?

846
01:10:35,631 --> 01:10:37,258
Now you know.

847
01:10:38,667 --> 01:10:40,658
That's not the worst part.

848
01:10:40,736 --> 01:10:42,670
What's the worst part?

849
01:10:42,738 --> 01:10:47,505
The worst part is that tomorrow you
will have forgotten all about this...

850
01:10:47,576 --> 01:10:50,807
and you'll treat me
like a jerk again.

851
01:10:50,879 --> 01:10:54,440
- It's all right. I am a jerk.
- You're not.

852
01:10:54,516 --> 01:10:56,575
It doesn't make any difference.

853
01:10:56,685 --> 01:11:01,315
I've killed myself so many times,
I don't even exist anymore.

854
01:11:01,390 --> 01:11:04,723
Sometimes I wish
I had a thousand lifetimes.

855
01:11:04,793 --> 01:11:08,422
I don't know, Phil.
Maybe it's not a curse.

856
01:11:08,463 --> 01:11:11,023
It just depends on
how you look at it.

857
01:11:12,801 --> 01:11:14,996
Gosh, you're an upbeat lady!

858
01:11:18,240 --> 01:11:22,734
- It's been a really nice day for me.
- Me too.

859
01:11:22,811 --> 01:11:27,839
Maybe, if it's not too boring,
we could do it again sometime.

860
01:11:27,916 --> 01:11:29,850
I hope so.

861
01:11:41,797 --> 01:11:43,355
You're still here.

862
01:11:44,966 --> 01:11:48,902
I thought you were supposed
to disappear or I was or something!

863
01:11:48,970 --> 01:11:51,438
Not until 6:00.

864
01:11:51,506 --> 01:11:53,167
You rat!

865
01:11:53,241 --> 01:11:54,970
I never said midnight.

866
01:11:55,043 --> 01:12:00,003
- You knew I was waiting for midnight!
- Does this mean you're gonna leave?

867
01:12:03,452 --> 01:12:04,919
Good.

868
01:12:15,597 --> 01:12:17,064
I'm sorry.

869
01:12:18,834 --> 01:12:21,997
It's all right.
You can fall asleep.

870
01:12:22,070 --> 01:12:26,404
I promise
I won't touch you, much.

871
01:12:27,642 --> 01:12:31,078
That's all right.
I'm not tired.

872
01:12:31,146 --> 01:12:33,171
What were you saying?

873
01:12:34,382 --> 01:12:37,715
I think the last thing
that you heard was...

874
01:12:37,819 --> 01:12:40,344
"Only God can make a tree."

875
01:12:40,422 --> 01:12:41,855
Really?

876
01:13:20,128 --> 01:13:22,062
What I wanted to say was...

877
01:13:24,099 --> 01:13:29,435
I think you're the kindest, sweetest,
prettiest person...

878
01:13:29,504 --> 01:13:31,597
I've ever met in my life.

879
01:13:33,108 --> 01:13:35,838
I've never seen anyone...

880
01:13:35,911 --> 01:13:38,311
that's nicer to people
than you are.

881
01:13:51,526 --> 01:13:54,393
The first time I saw you...

882
01:13:54,462 --> 01:13:57,989
something happened to me.

883
01:13:58,066 --> 01:14:00,466
I never told you, but...

884
01:14:03,605 --> 01:14:08,167
I knew that I wanted
to hold you as hard as I could.

885
01:14:21,022 --> 01:14:24,185
I don't deserve someone like you.

886
01:14:27,295 --> 01:14:30,560
But if I ever could...

887
01:14:30,632 --> 01:14:32,998
I swear I would love you...

888
01:14:33,068 --> 01:14:35,195
for the rest of my life.

889
01:14:39,774 --> 01:14:41,833
Did you say something?

890
01:14:47,382 --> 01:14:48,781
Good night.

891
01:16:01,389 --> 01:16:03,789
Who wants coffee?
Get it while it's hot.

892
01:16:03,858 --> 01:16:05,621
Thanks, Phil.

893
01:16:05,694 --> 01:16:10,722
- Larry? Skim milk, two sugars.
- Thanks, Phil.

894
01:16:10,799 --> 01:16:13,393
- Pastry?
- We're just setting up.

895
01:16:13,435 --> 01:16:15,369
Take your pick.

896
01:16:16,604 --> 01:16:18,663
Thanks. Raspberry. Great.

897
01:16:18,740 --> 01:16:22,301
I was just talking with Buster Green,
the head groundhog honcho.

898
01:16:22,377 --> 01:16:25,369
He said if we set up over here,
we might get a better shot.

899
01:16:25,413 --> 01:16:28,109
- What do you think?
- Sounds good.

900
01:16:28,183 --> 01:16:29,616
What do you think?

901
01:16:30,919 --> 01:16:32,853
Let's go for it.

902
01:16:32,921 --> 01:16:35,913
- Good work.
- Maybe we'll get lucky.

903
01:16:36,024 --> 01:16:37,924
Let me help you
with the heavy stuff.

904
01:16:39,694 --> 01:16:42,629
You got your coffee.
I'll get it.

905
01:16:43,732 --> 01:16:45,666
We never talk.
Do you have kids?

906
01:17:20,402 --> 01:17:22,336
I'd like a piano lesson, please.

907
01:17:22,404 --> 01:17:26,807
I'm with a student now. If you come
back tomorrow, I can squeeze you in.

908
01:17:26,875 --> 01:17:30,072
I kind of want to get started.
I could give you $1,000.

909
01:17:32,313 --> 01:17:33,712
Come on in.

910
01:17:53,435 --> 01:17:55,528
Good morning!
Off to see the groundhog?

911
01:17:58,673 --> 01:18:01,233
You think it will be
an early spring?

912
01:18:01,309 --> 01:18:03,800
"Winter slumbering in the open air...

913
01:18:03,878 --> 01:18:05,812
wears on his smiling face...

914
01:18:05,880 --> 01:18:07,848
a dream of spring."

915
01:18:49,924 --> 01:18:51,391
How's she look?

916
01:18:51,426 --> 01:18:53,986
- Great.
- Thank you.

917
01:18:54,062 --> 01:18:56,030
Did you know
he could ice sculpt?

918
01:19:11,813 --> 01:19:14,907
Not bad.
You say this is your first lesson?

919
01:19:15,850 --> 01:19:18,580
My father was a piano mover.

920
01:19:25,160 --> 01:19:27,321
I thought it was you.

921
01:19:31,232 --> 01:19:33,826
I have missed you so much.

922
01:19:37,805 --> 01:19:41,741
I don't know where you're headed,
but can you call in sick?

923
01:19:45,180 --> 01:19:47,842
I gotta get going.

924
01:19:47,916 --> 01:19:49,975
It's good to see you.

925
01:20:08,069 --> 01:20:10,264
Hello, father.

926
01:20:10,338 --> 01:20:13,796
Let's get you someplace warm.

927
01:20:13,875 --> 01:20:15,342
Remember me?

928
01:20:20,448 --> 01:20:23,508
Excuse me, sir. Are you the one
who brought the old man in?

929
01:20:23,585 --> 01:20:25,576
How is he?

930
01:20:25,653 --> 01:20:28,019
He just passed away.

931
01:20:29,290 --> 01:20:31,224
What did he die of?

932
01:20:31,292 --> 01:20:34,523
He was just old.
It was just his time.

933
01:20:37,365 --> 01:20:40,391
- I want to see his chart. Excuse me.
- Sir!

934
01:20:40,468 --> 01:20:42,629
You can't come in here.

935
01:20:42,704 --> 01:20:45,400
This is a restricted area.

936
01:20:54,415 --> 01:20:56,610
Where's the chart?

937
01:20:56,684 --> 01:20:59,881
Sometimes people just die.

938
01:20:59,954 --> 01:21:01,888
Not today.

939
01:21:13,735 --> 01:21:15,669
It's hard down there
at the bottom.

940
01:21:18,906 --> 01:21:21,568
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

941
01:21:25,913 --> 01:21:27,904
Come on, Dad!
Come on, Pop!

942
01:21:31,953 --> 01:21:34,581
Breathe, Pop!

943
01:22:01,115 --> 01:22:03,709
When Chekhov
saw the long winter...

944
01:22:03,785 --> 01:22:07,687
he saw a winter bleak and dark
and bereft of hope.

945
01:22:07,755 --> 01:22:12,692
Yet we know that winter is just
another step in the cycle of life.

946
01:22:12,760 --> 01:22:16,628
But standing here
among the people of Punxsutawney...

947
01:22:16,698 --> 01:22:19,428
and basking in the warmth
of their hearths and hearts...

948
01:22:20,535 --> 01:22:22,799
I couldn't imagine a better fate...

949
01:22:22,870 --> 01:22:26,135
than a long and lustrous winter.

950
01:22:26,207 --> 01:22:29,199
From Punxsutawney,
it's Phil Connors.

951
01:22:29,277 --> 01:22:30,710
So long.

952
01:22:32,413 --> 01:22:34,381
Very nice speech, Phil.

953
01:22:34,415 --> 01:22:36,747
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

954
01:22:36,818 --> 01:22:40,049
- How was that for you two?
- Man, you touched me.

955
01:22:40,121 --> 01:22:42,055
- Thanks, Larry.
- Thank you.

956
01:22:43,591 --> 01:22:45,855
I gotta go.

957
01:22:45,927 --> 01:22:50,125
That was surprising.
I didn't know you were so versatile.

958
01:22:50,198 --> 01:22:52,132
I surprise myself sometimes.

959
01:22:52,200 --> 01:22:54,259
Would you like
to get some coffee?

960
01:22:54,369 --> 01:22:58,328
I'd love to. Can I have a rain check?
I've got some errands to run.

961
01:23:02,009 --> 01:23:05,945
What errands?
I thought we were going back.

962
01:23:15,623 --> 01:23:17,420
Hold it, fella!

963
01:23:24,232 --> 01:23:27,065
What do you say?

964
01:23:27,135 --> 01:23:30,571
You little brat.
You have never thanked me!

965
01:23:30,638 --> 01:23:33,903
I'll see you tomorrow, maybe!

966
01:23:41,015 --> 01:23:43,745
- Now what?
- You've totaled it.

967
01:23:43,818 --> 01:23:48,915
It's only a flat tire.
Now just be patient. Just cool it!

968
01:23:48,990 --> 01:23:52,892
- It's an earthquake!
- It's not an earthquake!

969
01:23:52,960 --> 01:23:54,393
What is it?

970
01:23:57,665 --> 01:23:59,758
Thank you, young man.

971
01:24:00,902 --> 01:24:03,393
It's nothing.
I had the tire and the jack.

972
01:24:03,471 --> 01:24:06,167
Just be comfortable.
Be a minute.

973
01:24:06,240 --> 01:24:07,764
Who is that?

974
01:24:07,842 --> 01:24:10,606
Must be from the motor club.

975
01:24:12,113 --> 01:24:14,809
- My God! He's having a heart attack!
- What should I do?

976
01:24:14,882 --> 01:24:18,283
- Call an ambulance, a lawyer, a doctor!
- Mom, I don't think he's breathing!

977
01:24:26,227 --> 01:24:28,161
I think that did it.

978
01:24:31,599 --> 01:24:34,534
If you're gonna eat steak,
get some sharper teeth.

979
01:24:34,602 --> 01:24:37,298
- Enjoy your lunch.
- Thank you.

980
01:24:37,371 --> 01:24:40,101
Who was that? I'm fine.

981
01:24:40,174 --> 01:24:42,972
- Are you sure?
- Oh, yes. Eat.

982
01:24:47,381 --> 01:24:50,043
People just don't understand
what is involved in this.

983
01:24:50,117 --> 01:24:52,051
This is an art form.

984
01:24:52,119 --> 01:24:54,849
You know, I think most people
just think that...

985
01:24:54,922 --> 01:24:58,085
I hold the camera
and point it at stuff.

986
01:24:58,159 --> 01:25:00,627
There is a lot more to it
than just that.

987
01:25:02,530 --> 01:25:05,829
Would you be at all interested
in seeing the inside of the van?

988
01:25:05,900 --> 01:25:09,802
You know, I really have to get back
to the party.

989
01:25:09,871 --> 01:25:13,830
Great idea. I'll go with you.
Let me just drop a tip here.

990
01:25:20,948 --> 01:25:23,815
How are you?
Rita, this is Nancy.

991
01:25:23,885 --> 01:25:26,319
We were just going
to the party.

992
01:25:26,387 --> 01:25:28,321
- You going?
- Sounds like fun.

993
01:25:28,389 --> 01:25:30,983
Maybe we should call Phil.

994
01:25:31,058 --> 01:25:33,117
- I think he's already in there.
- Great.

995
01:27:29,810 --> 01:27:32,608
- Isn't he good?
- He's great!

996
01:27:32,713 --> 01:27:34,647
He's my student.

997
01:27:36,951 --> 01:27:38,885
I'm so proud.

998
01:27:40,021 --> 01:27:41,420
Thank you.

999
01:27:42,423 --> 01:27:44,482
Welcome to our party.

1000
01:27:44,558 --> 01:27:48,358
- I didn't know you could play like that.
- I'm versatile.

1001
01:27:56,303 --> 01:27:59,329
It's that nice, young man
from the motor club.

1002
01:27:59,407 --> 01:28:02,706
- Thank you again.
- It's nothing, ladies.

1003
01:28:02,777 --> 01:28:06,178
He's the fastest jack
in Jefferson County.

1004
01:28:08,516 --> 01:28:10,450
What was that all about?

1005
01:28:10,518 --> 01:28:13,544
I really don't know.
They've been hitting on me all night.

1006
01:28:14,422 --> 01:28:15,889
There you are.

1007
01:28:17,758 --> 01:28:21,159
I never thanked you properly
for what you did for Buster.

1008
01:28:21,228 --> 01:28:23,560
He would have choked for sure.

1009
01:28:23,631 --> 01:28:27,465
He may have.
He was trying to swallow a whole cow.

1010
01:28:27,535 --> 01:28:31,631
- I owe you one, buddy.
- Hang onto him, dear. He's a real find.

1011
01:28:34,508 --> 01:28:38,069
- What did you do today?
- Same old, same old.

1012
01:28:43,718 --> 01:28:45,413
Excuse me.

1013
01:28:45,486 --> 01:28:47,420
Fred, how was the wedding?

1014
01:28:47,488 --> 01:28:50,685
I just wanted to thank you
for making Debbie go through with it.

1015
01:28:50,791 --> 01:28:53,954
All I did was fan the flame
of her passion for you.

1016
01:28:54,028 --> 01:28:56,588
You are the best.

1017
01:28:56,664 --> 01:28:59,929
Rita,
this is Debbie and Fred Kleiser.

1018
01:29:00,000 --> 01:29:03,265
- Here you go, kids. Congratulations.
- What is this?

1019
01:29:03,337 --> 01:29:06,431
No way!

1020
01:29:06,507 --> 01:29:07,974
Wrestlemania!

1021
01:29:10,544 --> 01:29:13,604
How did you know?
We're gonna be in Pittsburgh anyway!

1022
01:29:13,681 --> 01:29:17,549
- Thank you! You're a real pal!
- This is the best!

1023
01:29:22,556 --> 01:29:26,356
- I don't understand.
- I guess not.

1024
01:29:26,393 --> 01:29:28,884
How does everyone know you?
You only come here once a year.

1025
01:29:28,963 --> 01:29:31,488
You seem like the most popular person
in town.

1026
01:29:31,565 --> 01:29:33,931
Excuse me. Dr. Connors?

1027
01:29:34,001 --> 01:29:36,799
I want to thank you
for fixing Felix's back.

1028
01:29:36,871 --> 01:29:39,237
He can even help
around the house again.

1029
01:29:39,306 --> 01:29:41,774
I'm sorry to hear that, Felix.

1030
01:29:44,278 --> 01:29:46,212
"Dr. Connors"?

1031
01:29:46,280 --> 01:29:48,840
It's kind of an honorary title.

1032
01:29:48,916 --> 01:29:51,680
- What is going on?
- I really don't know.

1033
01:29:51,786 --> 01:29:55,017
There is something
going on with you.

1034
01:29:55,089 --> 01:29:57,182
Would you like the long version
or the short one?

1035
01:29:57,258 --> 01:30:00,022
Let's start with the short
and go from there.

1036
01:30:05,733 --> 01:30:08,497
Okay, folks. Attention.

1037
01:30:08,569 --> 01:30:11,936
Time for the big bachelor auction.
You all know the rules.

1038
01:30:12,006 --> 01:30:14,440
All the eligible bachelors
come down in front...

1039
01:30:14,508 --> 01:30:17,773
and you ladies bid on them!

1040
01:30:17,878 --> 01:30:21,939
You get to do whatever you want
with them. No questions asked!

1041
01:30:22,016 --> 01:30:25,281
I don't want to know about it,
as long as it's legal!

1042
01:30:25,352 --> 01:30:29,152
Get out your pocketbooks and remember,
it's all for charity!

1043
01:30:32,092 --> 01:30:35,391
What are you doing down here?
Go on. Get up there.

1044
01:30:35,429 --> 01:30:38,956
I got ten bucks that
says you're mine!

1045
01:30:39,033 --> 01:30:42,491
- Buster, I got your first victim.
- Come up here!

1046
01:30:48,909 --> 01:30:52,276
All right! What am I bid
for this fine specimen?

1047
01:30:52,346 --> 01:30:53,973
Five dollars!

1048
01:30:54,048 --> 01:30:56,141
The bidding has begun
at five dollars.

1049
01:30:56,217 --> 01:30:59,118
- Ten dollars!
- Fifteen!

1050
01:30:59,186 --> 01:31:01,313
- Twenty!
- Twenty-five!

1051
01:31:01,388 --> 01:31:03,549
- Thirty!
- Thirty-five!

1052
01:31:03,624 --> 01:31:05,649
- Forty!
- Forty-five!

1053
01:31:05,726 --> 01:31:08,593
- Fifty!
- Fifty-five!

1054
01:31:08,662 --> 01:31:11,654
- Sixty!
- I'm bid sixty. Do I hear more?

1055
01:31:15,536 --> 01:31:18,733
Three hundred and thirty-nine dollars
and eighty-eight cents!

1056
01:31:23,510 --> 01:31:26,570
We can't accept any more bids.
That's sold...

1057
01:31:26,647 --> 01:31:30,344
to the little lady for $339.88!

1058
01:31:31,418 --> 01:31:32,817
Congratulations.

1059
01:31:40,928 --> 01:31:42,828
Okay, bachelors!
Who's next?

1060
01:31:52,907 --> 01:31:56,536
All right!
What am I bid for this guy?

1061
01:31:56,610 --> 01:31:58,601
Do I hear a buck and a half?

1062
01:31:58,679 --> 01:32:00,977
Anybody?

1063
01:32:01,048 --> 01:32:04,074
- Seventy-five cents?
- I bid two bits!

1064
01:32:04,151 --> 01:32:07,086
Sold to the lady
for twenty-five cents!

1065
01:32:07,154 --> 01:32:08,746
I got him!

1066
01:32:17,164 --> 01:32:19,826
Phil Connors!
I thought that was you!

1067
01:32:19,934 --> 01:32:22,630
This is Ned Ryerson,
my new insurance agent.

1068
01:32:22,703 --> 01:32:24,170
I'll say!

1069
01:32:25,239 --> 01:32:27,332
I have not seen this guy
for 20 years.

1070
01:32:27,408 --> 01:32:30,377
He comes to me and buys whole life,
term, uniflex...

1071
01:32:30,411 --> 01:32:32,436
fire, theft, auto,
dental, health...

1072
01:32:32,513 --> 01:32:35,710
with the optional death
and dismemberment plan, water damage.

1073
01:32:35,783 --> 01:32:38,217
This is the best day of my life.

1074
01:32:38,285 --> 01:32:40,446
Mine too.

1075
01:32:40,521 --> 01:32:43,752
- Where are we going?
- Let's not spoil it.

1076
01:32:46,660 --> 01:32:48,127
I got that!

1077
01:32:51,131 --> 01:32:54,589
- Why can't I look?
- Because you bother me a lot.

1078
01:32:54,668 --> 01:32:58,160
I'm getting cold.
How much longer do I have to sit here?

1079
01:32:58,238 --> 01:33:01,867
I'm just giving you your money's worth.
You paid top dollar for me.

1080
01:33:01,976 --> 01:33:04,774
I think you were a bargain.

1081
01:33:04,845 --> 01:33:07,746
Sweet of you to say.
You're probably right.

1082
01:33:10,551 --> 01:33:13,213
- Is it finished yet?
- Almost.

1083
01:33:13,287 --> 01:33:17,121
I still have to put cherry syrup on top
and then we can eat it.

1084
01:33:17,191 --> 01:33:19,853
Come on!
I'm freezing!

1085
01:33:19,927 --> 01:33:22,794
One second. All right.
Let me turn toward the light.

1086
01:33:29,336 --> 01:33:30,769
It's amazing.

1087
01:33:31,472 --> 01:33:33,406
It's beautiful.

1088
01:33:37,077 --> 01:33:40,911
- How did you do that?
- I know your face so well...

1089
01:33:41,015 --> 01:33:43,074
I could have done it
with my eyes closed.

1090
01:33:47,688 --> 01:33:51,624
It's lovely.
I don't know what to say.

1091
01:33:52,860 --> 01:33:54,327
I do.

1092
01:33:56,096 --> 01:33:58,564
No matter what happens tomorrow...

1093
01:33:58,632 --> 01:34:00,657
or for the rest of my life...

1094
01:34:00,734 --> 01:34:04,500
I'm happy now
because I love you.

1095
01:34:06,240 --> 01:34:08,174
I think I'm happy too.

1096
01:35:06,667 --> 01:35:09,295
- Please, not again.
- That is a great song!

1097
01:35:09,369 --> 01:35:10,961
- It's not!
- Don't listen to this man...

1098
01:35:13,173 --> 01:35:15,471
It's too early.

1099
01:35:25,986 --> 01:35:28,386
Something is different.

1100
01:35:28,422 --> 01:35:29,889
Good or bad?

1101
01:35:29,957 --> 01:35:32,448
Anything different is good...

1102
01:35:34,728 --> 01:35:36,889
but this could be real good.

1103
01:35:41,802 --> 01:35:43,736
Why are you here?

1104
01:35:43,804 --> 01:35:46,238
I bought you. I own you.

1105
01:35:48,275 --> 01:35:50,209
But why are you still here?

1106
01:35:50,277 --> 01:35:52,939
You said stay, so I stayed.

1107
01:35:55,916 --> 01:35:58,214
I said stay, so you stayed?

1108
01:35:58,285 --> 01:36:00,947
I can't even make a collie stay.

1109
01:36:02,890 --> 01:36:05,688
I gotta check something.

1110
01:36:05,759 --> 01:36:07,226
Stay.

1111
01:36:14,201 --> 01:36:15,600
They're gone!

1112
01:36:16,503 --> 01:36:18,562
They're all gone!

1113
01:36:20,174 --> 01:36:22,972
- Do you know what today is?
- What?

1114
01:36:24,344 --> 01:36:26,710
Today is tomorrow.

1115
01:36:26,780 --> 01:36:28,475
It happened.

1116
01:36:30,417 --> 01:36:32,612
- You're here.
- I'm here.

1117
01:36:36,557 --> 01:36:41,153
Why weren't you like this last night?
You just fell sleep.

1118
01:36:43,363 --> 01:36:45,831
It was the end
of a very long day.

1119
01:36:49,236 --> 01:36:52,831
Is there anything
I can do for you today?

1120
01:36:52,906 --> 01:36:56,273
I'm sure I can think
of something.

1121
01:37:29,643 --> 01:37:31,577
It's so beautiful!

1122
01:37:42,256 --> 01:37:44,156
Let's live here.

1123
01:37:54,368 --> 01:37:56,427
We'll rent to start.
